About how ad ds server work:
step 1: Client send AS-REQ to server
Client use your entered password to create an hash key use an hash function, we call that secret key, then, use current time on the client and encrypt that with secret key
Which, is called PA-ENC-TIMESTAMP, then send to server.


step 2: Server receive, 
B1: server use secret key which is saved on server to decrypt that packet

there are two cases
+ Correct password: Server send back a KBR-AS-REP packet
Packet type: 11 (AS-rep)
Status: Success
In payload is the ticket and Enc-part to give the client session key to work with
- Wrong password: server send back KRB_error
Packet type: 30 (KRB-error)
Status: Failure
In payload is error-code:
KDC_ERR_PREAUTH_FAILED: 24: account exist, but wrong password
KDC_ERR_C_PRINCIPAL_UNKNOWN: 6: account not exist
KDC_ERR_CLIENT_REVOKED: 18 Account is locked or disable


